      • uploadToDataStore

        private com.google.appengine.api.datastore.Entity uploadToDataStore(java.util.List<com.google.cloud.vision.v1.ColorInfo> dominantColors,
                                                                    java.lang.String imageLink,
                                                                    com.google.appengine.api.datastore.DatastoreService datastore,
                                                                    java.lang.String userID,
                                                                    java.lang.String photoID)
        This function receives the data obtained from the data store and stores it in the google data store. In addition, it builds a json string using the obtained information and saves it to the data store. Instead of the returned ColorInfo object that the cloud vision API returns.
        Parameters:
        dominantColors - ColorInfo Object, returned from vision API
        imageLink - String image URL retrieved from Facebook
        datastore - Google Data Store Service
        userID - Passed user's identification number
        photoID - Passed photo's identification number
        Returns:
        Google Data Store Entity or null

      • getDominantColors

        private java.util.List<com.google.cloud.vision.v1.ColorInfo> getDominantColors(java.lang.String imageLink)
                                                                        throws java.lang.Exception
        This function receives a String link to an image, then proceeds to call the downloadFile function which returns a byte []. Then using that, calls the cloud vision API requesting the IMAGE_PROPERTIES type and stores the returned result in a ColorInfo object. This object is then returned to the calling function.
        Parameters:
        imageLink - String image URL retrieved from Facebook
        Returns:
        ColorInfo Object, returned from vision API
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - Handle Exceptions
